name: Drones
summary: Recent sightings of large drones in New Jersey have sparked concern and speculation. Despite numerous reports, the U.S. remains skeptical about their origin or purpose. Authorities in Philadelphia are also investigating drone sightings, while a congressman suggests the mysterious drones may be from an Iranian mothership offshore. However, the governor of New Jersey assures the public the drones do not pose a safety concern. The Wall Street Journal reports on one resident's attempts to track down the drones. Amidst the sightings, the FAA has implemented flight restrictions, and mayors in New Jersey have demanded action. NBC News provides an overview of the situation and confirms the Department of Defense's readiness to respond if the drones pose a threat to military assets. The continued drone sightings have puzzled residents and officials alike, and further investigation is underway.

name: Friday the 13th
summary: Today is Friday the 13th, a date that has long been associated with bad luck and superstition. The origins of this superstition can be traced back to ancient folklore and religious beliefs. In Christianity, the number 13 is considered unlucky because there were 13 people present at the Last Supper, including Jesus and the 12 apostles. Friday is also considered unlucky in some cultures, as it was the day that Jesus was crucified. As a result, Friday the 13th has become a day that many people avoid making important decisions or taking risks. However, some people believe that the superstition is simply a myth and that Friday the 13th is no different than any other day. Today is also a popular day for tattoos, with many tattoo shops offering discounts and deals.

The uniforms worn by the teams during the game have undergone changes over time, adding to the spectacle of the event. In 2024, the game will be held in Maryland, and the offenses of both teams are expected to perform differently from previous years. The buildup to the game includes the Game Ball Run, where players from both teams collaborate to cover over 350 miles. The rivalry between Army and Navy is celebrated as a representation of the spirit of college football, a clash that carries deep meaning for both institutions. name: Polio vaccine
summary: Robert F. Kennedy Jr.'s lawyer has petitioned the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) to revoke its approval of the polio vaccine. The lawyer, who is also a top ally of Kennedy Jr., argues that the vaccine is unsafe and has caused serious health problems, including paralysis. The FDA has not yet responded to the petition, but the move has sparked backlash from public health experts and politicians. Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell has warned Kennedy Jr. against undermining trust in vaccines, while the Democratic National Committee has released a report criticizing the effort. The petition has also drawn attention to the growing anti-vaccine movement, which has been linked to outbreaks of preventable diseases.
